WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.330
[Characters, behaviors, places,
organizations, and events shown in the series

00:00:02.400 --> 00:00:04.800
are entirely fictional,
are solely for entertainment purposes,

00:00:04.830 --> 00:00:07.800
with no intention to instruct
or promote any kind of behavior;

00:00:07.830 --> 00:00:10.000
viewer discretion is advised]

00:00:10.230 --> 00:00:12.300
What? What's going on?

00:00:12.530 --> 00:00:13.530
Does your head hurt?

00:00:16.230 --> 00:00:16.770
Hey!

00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:18.300
I really like her.

00:00:18.470 --> 00:00:19.400
- Huh?!
- What?!

00:00:19.470 --> 00:00:22.100
How can I take care of you
while I'm asleep?

00:00:22.530 --> 00:00:25.200
"To tell you the truth,
the warden has been onto you for a while."

00:00:25.270 --> 00:00:26.370
Run, Z.

00:00:28.030 --> 00:00:29.970
"If you get caught,
you'll face serious punishment

00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:32.000
because she's extremely angry.

00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:35.030
The best way to go from here
is to keep running."

00:00:36.030 --> 00:00:36.900
Whoa!

00:00:43.270 --> 00:00:44.330
Where did she go?

00:00:46.230 --> 00:00:47.230
I don't know.

00:00:49.930 --> 00:00:51.070
Let's get out of here.

00:00:52.170 --> 00:00:53.100
Where to?

00:00:53.530 --> 00:00:54.370
I don't know,

00:00:54.930 --> 00:00:56.470
just anywhere but here,

00:00:56.530 --> 00:00:57.370
and...

00:00:57.730 --> 00:00:58.900
away from her.

00:03:01.230 --> 00:03:06.070
Please suspend your mission
to track down Angel No. Z328.

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:08.300
Why did you summon me back here?

00:03:08.870 --> 00:03:10.070
What did I do wrong?

00:03:10.670 --> 00:03:15.470
Please suspend your mission
to track down Angel No. Z328.

00:03:16.270 --> 00:03:17.730
She's violating the rules.

00:03:18.930 --> 00:03:20.470
I was simply doing my job.

00:03:21.030 --> 00:03:26.329
Since Miss Jenika, user No. 59342,

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:30.800
has requested a second wish 12 hours ago,

00:03:30.829 --> 00:03:35.329
we have proceeded with the approval
and deducted the points redeemed.

00:03:37.400 --> 00:03:38.570
A second wish?

00:03:40.500 --> 00:03:41.829
What did that child request?

00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:47.970
Miss Jenika's second wish states,

00:03:48.030 --> 00:03:50.829
"I wish all the struggles
would disappear from whom I love."

00:03:50.870 --> 00:03:55.470
I repeat, "I wish all the struggles
would disappear from whom I love."

00:03:56.870 --> 00:03:57.870
How did this happen?

00:04:10.830 --> 00:04:11.830
Whoa!

00:04:13.430 --> 00:04:14.470
Look at the view!

00:04:14.500 --> 00:04:15.370
Isn't it pretty?

00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:20.200
Isn't it?

00:04:22.230 --> 00:04:22.970
Mm.

00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:25.230
It's pretty good.

00:04:26.530 --> 00:04:28.730
Come on, let's look at the room.

00:04:29.100 --> 00:04:29.900
Let's go.

00:04:31.830 --> 00:04:33.300
Wow!

00:04:33.930 --> 00:04:37.870
Fortunately, the voucher
that Jin gave me hasn't expired.

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:47.670
Look, there are
two glasses and four pillows.

00:04:47.930 --> 00:04:49.570
The A/C is nice and cool,

00:04:49.630 --> 00:04:50.630
and the room is so spacious.

00:04:51.130 --> 00:04:52.370
This is so heavenly!

00:04:59.230 --> 00:05:02.630
Hey, are you gonna be
all gloomy throughout the trip,

00:05:02.730 --> 00:05:03.970
milk-breath angel?

00:05:05.200 --> 00:05:07.330
I'm bringing you out here for a vacation.

00:05:07.800 --> 00:05:09.370
It's not often we get to do this.

00:05:09.430 --> 00:05:11.500
See? The hotel is beautiful.

00:05:13.630 --> 00:05:15.570
Don't you feel anything

00:05:16.230 --> 00:05:17.700
about what she said earlier?

00:05:19.200 --> 00:05:22.130
The one where she mentioned
that I only had a little time left.

00:05:31.230 --> 00:05:32.430
That's exactly why

00:05:33.530 --> 00:05:37.170
I want to make every second count.

00:05:40.900 --> 00:05:42.730
Come on, just gimme a little smile.

00:05:42.930 --> 00:05:43.670
Come on.

00:05:49.230 --> 00:05:50.430
Whoa, look.

00:05:53.200 --> 00:05:54.200
We also have these.

00:05:56.730 --> 00:05:57.730
A pair of swans.

00:06:01.330 --> 00:06:03.470
Look, they wrote our names down, too.

00:06:04.230 --> 00:06:07.370
"Welcome, Jane and Z."

00:06:10.130 --> 00:06:11.130
How adorable.

00:06:19.130 --> 00:06:20.130
Let's wash up.

00:06:24.170 --> 00:06:25.070
Wash up?

00:06:25.100 --> 00:06:25.770
Mm.

00:06:26.400 --> 00:06:27.200
Let's go.

00:06:52.930 --> 00:06:54.330
There you go.

00:06:55.500 --> 00:06:57.000
- Are you done?
- Mm.

00:06:58.870 --> 00:06:59.870
Show me.

00:07:04.530 --> 00:07:05.570
You're pretty good at this.

00:07:09.700 --> 00:07:10.770
Let's eat this.

00:07:10.830 --> 00:07:12.630
Look! It's so mouthwatering.

00:07:12.900 --> 00:07:14.270
Wow.

00:07:30.030 --> 00:07:31.270
By the way...

00:07:33.430 --> 00:07:34.900
How can you be sure

00:07:35.330 --> 00:07:37.870
that the warden won't find us?

00:07:42.300 --> 00:07:43.100
Look.

00:07:45.200 --> 00:07:48.430
This morning, we missed out on this part.

00:07:48.600 --> 00:07:49.530
Read it.

00:07:51.030 --> 00:07:53.930
"How to disable Z's tracking:

00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:58.030
go to Settings, then Privacy,

00:07:58.470 --> 00:08:00.530
and User's Assistant Tracking."

00:08:00.730 --> 00:08:03.200
That's what it takes
to keep her from finding us.

00:08:03.400 --> 00:08:05.200
Safe and sound!

00:08:06.400 --> 00:08:07.170
Mm.

00:08:08.600 --> 00:08:09.300
Mm!

00:09:17.870 --> 00:09:20.370
Being in a relationship is this nice, huh?

00:09:24.430 --> 00:09:25.330
In a relationship?

00:09:26.500 --> 00:09:28.130
Who's in a relationship with who?

00:09:35.030 --> 00:09:36.930
You and I, of course.

00:09:37.600 --> 00:09:38.830
You and I?

00:09:39.330 --> 00:09:40.030
Mm!

00:09:42.900 --> 00:09:44.670
When did we make it official?

00:09:45.500 --> 00:09:46.170
Huh?

00:09:46.770 --> 00:09:48.270
Why would you ask that?

00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:51.630
Well...

00:09:52.730 --> 00:09:55.500
I didn't realize...

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:57.470
when we became girlfriends.

00:09:58.270 --> 00:09:59.530
Ugh!

00:10:01.470 --> 00:10:03.070
We confessed,

00:10:03.100 --> 00:10:05.300
smooched, kissed,

00:10:05.330 --> 00:10:06.830
and even held hands.

00:10:07.130 --> 00:10:08.800
If that's not being in a relationship,
I don't know what is.

00:10:09.270 --> 00:10:10.370
Are you...

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:12.270
breaking up with me?

00:10:12.470 --> 00:10:13.630
I'm not!

00:10:14.370 --> 00:10:18.700
Well, I just didn't realize
we can call ourselves girlfriends now.

00:10:27.230 --> 00:10:28.500
We could have, for a long time.

00:10:37.700 --> 00:10:38.700
But...

00:10:40.030 --> 00:10:41.830
how could I be your girlfriend

00:10:42.700 --> 00:10:47.430
when I'm not gonna be here
in this world with you for long?

00:10:55.270 --> 00:10:56.000
Listen,

00:10:56.630 --> 00:11:01.130
I don't know
how much time we have left,

00:11:02.670 --> 00:11:05.770
but right at this moment,

00:11:06.270 --> 00:11:07.270
and right here,

00:11:09.830 --> 00:11:11.970
you and I...

00:11:13.670 --> 00:11:15.270
we're officially together.

00:11:19.330 --> 00:11:21.330
I want this to last for a long, long time.

00:11:26.600 --> 00:11:27.870
So do I.

00:12:25.270 --> 00:12:26.700
You're pretty good-looking,

00:12:27.130 --> 00:12:28.230
babe.

00:12:29.900 --> 00:12:31.300
You're just laying it on thick.

00:12:32.370 --> 00:12:33.970
I'm not!

00:12:34.330 --> 00:12:35.630
It's the truth.

00:12:44.100 --> 00:12:45.100
So...

00:12:46.200 --> 00:12:47.870
I haven't been in a relationship before.

00:12:49.030 --> 00:12:53.070
What do couples

00:12:55.800 --> 00:12:57.000
usually do?

00:13:04.470 --> 00:13:05.470
Hey!

00:13:06.700 --> 00:13:07.700
What are you even thinking about?

00:13:08.670 --> 00:13:09.470
What?

00:13:10.030 --> 00:13:12.770
Well, you asked.

00:13:15.530 --> 00:13:16.530
You dirty mind!

00:14:08.430 --> 00:14:09.330
Go to bed!

00:14:20.530 --> 00:14:22.400
Sweet dreams.

00:15:52.700 --> 00:15:53.830
Hello.

00:15:54.300 --> 00:15:55.430
I'm back.

00:15:56.000 --> 00:15:57.570
How's everything at the studio?

00:15:57.730 --> 00:15:58.930
Everything is good.

00:15:59.070 --> 00:16:00.330
Mm, that's great to hear.

00:16:00.800 --> 00:16:02.730
Did anyone contact me while I was away?

00:16:03.400 --> 00:16:05.670
There were two girls asking for you.

00:16:06.530 --> 00:16:07.530
Who?

00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:47.200
Good morning,

00:16:49.530 --> 00:16:50.400
Z,

00:16:52.130 --> 00:16:53.130
my baby.

00:16:56.070 --> 00:16:57.370
Morning to you, too,

00:16:58.200 --> 00:16:59.100
Jane,

00:17:00.130 --> 00:17:01.130
my baby.

00:17:04.930 --> 00:17:05.930
That's cute.

00:17:08.000 --> 00:17:08.730
Let's go.

00:17:10.800 --> 00:17:11.700
Where?

00:17:13.900 --> 00:17:15.000
Let's take a bath.

00:17:36.900 --> 00:17:38.030
Ta-da!

00:17:41.330 --> 00:17:42.230
Isn't it beautiful?

00:17:42.700 --> 00:17:43.830
It is.

00:17:45.130 --> 00:17:46.830
I did this for you.

00:17:47.270 --> 00:17:48.900
- You did?
- Mm.

00:17:57.230 --> 00:18:01.630
Earlier, you told me that

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:05.900
the less time we had,
the more we'd need to make it count.

00:18:10.930 --> 00:18:12.230
From here on out,

00:18:13.170 --> 00:18:15.300
I'll make you feel

00:18:15.800 --> 00:18:19.530
like the luckiest girl alive
to have me as your girlfriend.

00:18:23.630 --> 00:18:25.430
Which series did you steal that from?

00:18:37.100 --> 00:18:39.430
Wow, the water is still warm.

00:19:35.230 --> 00:19:36.270
Is it too hot?

00:19:38.230 --> 00:19:39.470
It's just right.

00:19:40.730 --> 00:19:42.100
Why are you so well-behaved today?

00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:47.130
You're just like a kitten.

00:19:51.830 --> 00:19:53.730
With this princess treatment,

00:19:54.500 --> 00:19:55.670
why would I be stubborn?

00:20:32.600 --> 00:20:34.300
Hello?

00:20:34.870 --> 00:20:37.730
Hello, may I speak to Miss Jane?

00:20:39.000 --> 00:20:40.900
This is she. Who am I speaking to?

00:20:41.170 --> 00:20:43.570
I'm a staff member from Bew's Studio.

00:20:43.800 --> 00:20:47.000
I'm calling to inform you she's returned
from her retreat this morning.

00:20:47.270 --> 00:20:49.800
Would you like to schedule a meeting?

00:21:45.300 --> 00:21:46.700
I'm back, Beam.

00:21:48.230 --> 00:21:49.730
I made merit on your behalf.

00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:04.530
I miss you.

00:22:16.030 --> 00:22:18.530
Are we going out?

00:22:21.000 --> 00:22:22.670
We're going back.

00:22:23.600 --> 00:22:24.470
Oh...

00:22:24.930 --> 00:22:26.970
Didn't you say
we were gonna be here a while?

00:22:28.330 --> 00:22:30.170
Aren't you worried
the warden's gonna come after us?

00:22:31.700 --> 00:22:35.900
Earlier, someone
from Bew's Studio just called.

00:22:36.300 --> 00:22:39.200
They told me Bew is back.

00:22:39.900 --> 00:22:42.170
She's ready to meet us now.

00:22:44.330 --> 00:22:48.900
If meeting Bew means less time with you,

00:22:50.230 --> 00:22:51.470
can I not go?

00:22:53.130 --> 00:22:56.370
Then, won't it keep bothering you?

00:22:59.400 --> 00:23:02.230
Not as bad
as having to sacrifice our time together.

00:23:04.300 --> 00:23:08.100
But... we've already come this far.

00:23:08.300 --> 00:23:09.430
It's only a bit more to go.

00:23:09.670 --> 00:23:10.630
I think...

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:13.030
I wanna find out.

00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:21.430
Please?

00:23:21.800 --> 00:23:23.400
I really wanna know.

00:23:23.670 --> 00:23:24.670
Let's just go.

00:23:28.600 --> 00:23:29.400
Mm.

00:23:30.330 --> 00:23:31.030
Fine.

00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:34.500
Whatever you say goes.

00:23:35.830 --> 00:23:39.570
After all, the app sent me to spoil you.

00:23:43.430 --> 00:23:46.930
So, are you still having a headache?

00:23:50.130 --> 00:23:52.170
No. It's all better now.

00:23:55.400 --> 00:23:57.170
Then, let's get going.

00:23:57.530 --> 00:23:59.470
We'll go home,
freshen up, and get changed.

00:24:00.070 --> 00:24:00.770
Mm.

00:24:01.000 --> 00:24:01.670
Come on.

00:24:44.300 --> 00:24:45.630
Are you Jane?

00:24:50.030 --> 00:24:51.130
Hello.

00:24:52.400 --> 00:24:55.230
I'm so sorry for taking up your time.

00:24:56.030 --> 00:24:57.230
It's alright.

00:24:57.900 --> 00:25:00.700
My assistant told me
that you were looking for someone.

00:25:01.500 --> 00:25:02.500
That's right.

00:25:11.830 --> 00:25:14.430
These are the lyrics to your song...

00:25:15.100 --> 00:25:16.200
right?

00:25:20.670 --> 00:25:28.670
♫I don't even know
it's possible for someone to be this cute♫

00:25:31.700 --> 00:25:33.400
Can I ask where you heard this from?

00:25:35.300 --> 00:25:36.300
So...

00:25:37.070 --> 00:25:40.800
a friend of mine sang it to me.

00:25:44.200 --> 00:25:45.970
The other day, when I came to see you,

00:25:46.400 --> 00:25:48.830
I was gonna ask you about this.

00:25:49.330 --> 00:25:50.930
Apart from Tony,

00:25:51.300 --> 00:25:53.330
have you ever sung
this song to anyone else?

00:25:55.330 --> 00:25:57.600
There were a couple of people...

00:25:59.330 --> 00:26:00.470
What's your friend's name?

00:26:01.330 --> 00:26:02.870
I called her...

00:26:03.930 --> 00:26:04.930
Z.

00:26:08.000 --> 00:26:09.200
Z?

00:26:13.130 --> 00:26:15.470
Let me play this for you.

00:26:17.900 --> 00:26:23.500
- ♫You secretly got my head in the clouds♫
- Here you go.

00:26:24.030 --> 00:26:30.270
- ♫Your smile almost got me on the ground♫
- Where did you get this file from?

00:26:35.000 --> 00:26:36.600
They really did know each other...

00:26:42.800 --> 00:26:43.800
Bew,

00:26:45.300 --> 00:26:48.970
I have someone I'd like you to meet.

00:27:11.630 --> 00:27:12.630
Bew.

00:27:45.400 --> 00:27:46.470
Beam?

00:27:52.100 --> 00:28:01.570
♫I don't even know
it's possible for someone to be this cute♫

00:28:01.800 --> 00:28:05.530
♫All I can do is look away♫

00:28:05.600 --> 00:28:10.100
♫I can never meet your eyes, oh-oh♫

00:28:10.470 --> 00:28:12.170
You keep singing this song, Bew.

00:28:12.770 --> 00:28:14.570
Well, I just so happen to like it.

00:28:15.200 --> 00:28:18.030
It's a shame
that the company wouldn't release it.

00:28:21.200 --> 00:28:26.300
♫Every time we meet, I control myself♫

00:28:26.330 --> 00:28:30.930
♫Not to shout how intensely I've felt♫

00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:34.130
♫Please, can you help me?♫

00:28:34.200 --> 00:28:37.500
♫Don't be this cute, please hear my plea♫

00:28:37.530 --> 00:28:42.370
♫Don't hurt me with your pretty smile♫

00:28:46.400 --> 00:28:47.530
Scoop the fried garlic.

00:28:47.600 --> 00:28:49.730
- That's not enough?
- Add more.

00:28:51.430 --> 00:28:52.430
Of course.

00:28:53.070 --> 00:28:53.800
Just a little more, alright?

00:28:53.870 --> 00:28:56.400
I'm home!

00:28:57.830 --> 00:28:59.100
What are you making?

00:28:59.400 --> 00:29:00.500
It's pork blood soup, sweetie.

00:29:00.530 --> 00:29:01.630
Guess whose favorite it is.

00:29:04.100 --> 00:29:07.200
I have something for you today.

00:29:10.030 --> 00:29:11.270
Here!

00:29:11.300 --> 00:29:14.530
- Wow!!
- Whoa!

00:29:14.600 --> 00:29:16.930
- Congrats!
- You did it again!

00:29:17.000 --> 00:29:19.870
Hey, I think it's gonna be real crowded
in the trophy cabinet.

00:29:19.900 --> 00:29:22.770
- See? I told you you'd win.
- Mm-hm.

00:29:23.030 --> 00:29:25.470
Today, I even sang in the large hall.

00:29:25.500 --> 00:29:27.030
- Wow!
- Great job!

00:29:27.330 --> 00:29:28.430
You wanna see the video?

00:29:28.500 --> 00:29:29.770
- Sure, let's watch it.
- We can eat later.

00:29:30.100 --> 00:29:31.100
Let's eat later.

00:29:31.470 --> 00:29:33.300
- So they record videos now, huh?
- My friend said...

00:29:33.370 --> 00:29:34.870
My friend did it for me.

00:29:34.900 --> 00:29:38.630
♫You're as lovely as the galaxy♫

00:29:38.700 --> 00:29:44.830
♫My heart's paper-thin when you smile at me♫

00:29:45.100 --> 00:29:48.900
♫You're as lovely as the galaxy♫

00:29:50.200 --> 00:29:51.070
Isn't it beautiful?

00:29:52.030 --> 00:29:52.770
Couldn't be more beautiful!

00:29:52.830 --> 00:29:55.230
You sang even better than last time.

00:29:55.830 --> 00:29:58.570
♫The Earth isn't big enough
for your cuteness♫

00:29:58.630 --> 00:30:01.270
That's mediocre. Not much of a talent.

00:30:02.130 --> 00:30:05.070
That's because she's Bew's sister.
Who'd dare knock her out?

00:30:05.330 --> 00:30:08.530
With this skill, she'd never make it
past the first round in typical competitions.

00:30:09.870 --> 00:30:12.070
Why does this always happen to me?

00:30:15.800 --> 00:30:18.830
No matter how many times I win,
I always see these horrible comments.

00:30:22.670 --> 00:30:24.870
Is it so wrong to be Bew's little sister?

00:30:28.230 --> 00:30:30.930
Don't dwell on these comments, sweetie.

00:30:32.200 --> 00:30:33.630
Beam, listen to me,

00:30:33.670 --> 00:30:35.170
the reason you've won

00:30:35.730 --> 00:30:37.330
was really because you've got skills.

00:30:38.630 --> 00:30:40.630
It didn't have anything to do
with you being my sister.

00:30:42.630 --> 00:30:45.730
I've worked in this industry for so long,
so you have to believe me.

00:30:45.800 --> 00:30:47.930
I can tell how great you are.

00:31:02.100 --> 00:31:03.330
I'm off, Mom.

00:31:12.870 --> 00:31:14.870
It's just so-so,
not outstanding or anything.

00:31:15.570 --> 00:31:17.170
She's never gonna be famous
from the look of it.

00:31:17.230 --> 00:31:18.930
She'll only win small competitions.

00:31:19.200 --> 00:31:21.330
It's really hard
for someone to take off with that.

00:31:21.470 --> 00:31:23.230
Can the judges reconsider?

00:31:23.270 --> 00:31:26.270
Why don't you just wish me dead
if you're gonna be this harsh?

00:31:26.300 --> 00:31:28.700
This kind of scoring
is not fair for other people one bit.

00:31:29.000 --> 00:31:30.630
The others
are a lot more talented than her.

00:31:38.670 --> 00:31:39.870
What's on your mind?

00:31:41.470 --> 00:31:42.970
Wanna listen to something nice?

00:31:43.200 --> 00:31:44.130
What is it?

00:31:44.200 --> 00:31:44.900
Here.

00:31:45.670 --> 00:31:51.200
♫You secretly got my head in the clouds♫

00:31:51.700 --> 00:31:57.830
♫Your smile almost got me on the ground♫

00:32:05.870 --> 00:32:08.900
Wow, that's such a beautiful song!

00:32:09.500 --> 00:32:12.500
The people who talk badly about her
are incredibly mean.

00:32:16.300 --> 00:32:17.800
I will find a way to prove to Beam

00:32:18.000 --> 00:32:21.670
that she has it in her to be an artist.

00:32:22.100 --> 00:32:23.400
What do you plan on doing?

00:32:23.900 --> 00:32:26.700
If my former producer hears this song,

00:32:27.730 --> 00:32:29.530
he will notice something extraordinary.

00:32:29.600 --> 00:32:30.900
This kid has a knack for it!

00:32:31.070 --> 00:32:33.930
But he was your producer.

00:32:34.130 --> 00:32:37.900
Beam will still think
it's out of respect for you.

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:41.330
I won't let him know I sent it in.

00:32:41.870 --> 00:32:44.270
I'll let this prove itself.

00:32:46.700 --> 00:32:48.000
It's beautiful, Mom.

00:32:48.070 --> 00:32:49.800
Take it from me. This is extraordinary.

00:33:02.000 --> 00:33:03.230
I remember now.

00:33:07.700 --> 00:33:08.700
My name is Beam.

00:33:12.030 --> 00:33:13.230
My older sister's name is Bew.

00:33:16.600 --> 00:33:17.830
I dreamed of being a singer.

00:33:21.100 --> 00:33:22.430
I love salmon

00:33:26.130 --> 00:33:27.370
and hate bean sprouts.

00:33:29.270 --> 00:33:30.900
I love watching 'Detective Conan.'

00:33:36.400 --> 00:33:37.400
Beam!

00:33:47.830 --> 00:33:49.670
I miss you so much!

00:33:55.100 --> 00:33:57.330
There wasn't a day I didn't miss you.

00:34:16.600 --> 00:34:18.429
It's just so-so,
not outstanding or anything.

00:34:18.900 --> 00:34:20.429
She's never gonna be famous
from the look of it.

00:34:20.500 --> 00:34:21.929
She'll only win small competitions.

00:34:22.000 --> 00:34:23.900
It's really hard
for someone to take off with that.

00:34:23.929 --> 00:34:25.800
Can the judges reconsider?

00:34:26.070 --> 00:34:27.500
The others
are a lot more talented than her.

00:34:27.530 --> 00:34:29.969
This kind of scoring
is not fair for other people one bit.

00:34:38.670 --> 00:34:41.300
That's mediocre. Not much of a talent.

00:34:43.230 --> 00:34:46.429
That's because she's Bew's sister.
Who'd dare knock her out?

00:34:47.330 --> 00:34:50.400
With this skill, she'd never make it
past the first round in typical competitions.

00:34:55.230 --> 00:34:56.929
There's no reason to try anymore.

00:35:28.670 --> 00:35:30.330
Do you still think about that moment?

00:35:32.830 --> 00:35:33.670
Mm.

00:35:43.830 --> 00:35:45.170
No matter what I do...

00:35:45.930 --> 00:35:47.630
I can't get rid of it, Jane.

00:36:28.400 --> 00:36:29.830
I'm so sorry.

00:36:37.200 --> 00:36:38.470
I really am.

00:36:42.600 --> 00:36:43.730
Why are you saying sorry?

00:36:53.230 --> 00:36:54.100
Well...

00:36:56.570 --> 00:36:57.970
I should have believed you.

00:37:11.430 --> 00:37:13.430
I shouldn't have brought you to see Bew.

00:37:22.600 --> 00:37:24.070
I made everything worse.

00:37:36.200 --> 00:37:37.530
It's fine, Jane.

00:37:51.770 --> 00:37:53.300
If I hadn't done it,

00:37:56.130 --> 00:37:57.330
everyone...

00:37:59.530 --> 00:38:02.570
would've been fine...

00:38:17.300 --> 00:38:18.500
Don't cry.

00:38:20.900 --> 00:38:21.900
I'm okay.

00:38:36.930 --> 00:38:38.530
I'm crying like a baby now.

00:38:40.330 --> 00:38:41.630
Why are you still crying, then?

00:38:42.670 --> 00:38:43.670
I don't know...

00:39:00.000 --> 00:39:01.270
The same goes to you, Z.

00:39:02.800 --> 00:39:05.070
Your face is all blotchy now.

00:40:41.600 --> 00:40:43.600
Can I spend all night with you?

00:41:42.470 --> 00:41:43.670
Are you awake, babe?

00:41:54.000 --> 00:41:55.430
Don't be so extra!

00:41:55.730 --> 00:41:57.930
What? All worn out?

00:42:00.000 --> 00:42:01.230
I don't know why,

00:42:01.900 --> 00:42:03.200
but I feel out of strength...

00:42:17.100 --> 00:42:18.500
You're not burning up.

00:42:20.300 --> 00:42:21.770
But your lips are so pale.

00:42:28.830 --> 00:42:29.830
Or...

00:42:30.600 --> 00:42:32.500
is this the consequence

00:42:33.270 --> 00:42:34.730
of finding out the truth?

00:42:40.100 --> 00:42:41.170
I don't know...

00:42:53.630 --> 00:42:55.470
Stay put. I'll be back.

00:43:00.270 --> 00:43:01.270
Don't move.

00:43:12.830 --> 00:43:13.630
Oh?

00:43:14.530 --> 00:43:15.530
Uncle Duang?

00:43:18.630 --> 00:43:20.030
Where have you been these several days?

00:43:20.800 --> 00:43:22.430
I didn't want to disappear,

00:43:23.400 --> 00:43:25.730
but I was also punished

00:43:25.800 --> 00:43:27.470
for being part of this whole thing.

00:43:29.100 --> 00:43:30.930
Uncle Duang, right now,

00:43:31.730 --> 00:43:33.430
Z isn't doing well.

00:43:34.230 --> 00:43:35.430
All of a sudden,

00:43:36.630 --> 00:43:37.700
she has no strength left.

00:43:39.830 --> 00:43:40.970
I always knew

00:43:41.670 --> 00:43:43.070
that this would happen.

00:43:44.630 --> 00:43:48.030
This is the first consequence
of violating the rules.

00:43:48.730 --> 00:43:50.000
The first consequence?

00:43:51.300 --> 00:43:52.370
So that means...

00:43:54.570 --> 00:43:55.870
there will be more?

00:43:56.830 --> 00:43:57.830
Of course.

00:43:58.500 --> 00:43:59.900
A lot more.

00:44:00.870 --> 00:44:04.200
The reason I came here today
is to tell you this.

00:44:05.670 --> 00:44:06.770
What is it?

00:44:12.230 --> 00:44:15.670
Earlier, Z still...

00:44:16.500 --> 00:44:18.130
had a month left with you, right?

00:44:20.300 --> 00:44:23.330
Right now,
there's less than a week left.

00:44:29.830 --> 00:44:31.130
Are you joking with me?

00:44:33.230 --> 00:44:34.130
No,

00:44:35.730 --> 00:44:36.930
I'm not joking with you.

00:44:39.730 --> 00:44:41.130
I'd like to warn you.

00:44:42.030 --> 00:44:44.130
If there's something you want to do,
just go for it,

00:44:44.900 --> 00:44:46.770
so you won't regret it.

00:44:53.500 --> 00:44:55.230
There's barely a week left?

00:45:31.630 --> 00:45:32.700
Does this ring a bell?

00:45:34.830 --> 00:45:35.670
Mm.

00:45:38.970 --> 00:45:40.070
That...

00:45:40.500 --> 00:45:41.600
was my room.

00:45:54.700 --> 00:45:56.530
You still look the same, sweetie.

00:45:57.300 --> 00:45:58.430
Your body is the same.

00:45:58.700 --> 00:46:00.500
Your face is the same.

00:46:01.100 --> 00:46:02.230
I'm so happy to see you.

00:46:04.870 --> 00:46:06.930
Thank you, Jane, for bringing Beam to us.

00:46:07.670 --> 00:46:08.730
My pleasure.

00:46:11.500 --> 00:46:13.830
Does she really have a week left with us?

00:46:16.000 --> 00:46:17.830
Just a week left?

00:46:22.100 --> 00:46:22.900
Yes.

00:46:23.870 --> 00:46:28.800
That's why I want her
to spend time with her family.

00:47:22.730 --> 00:47:25.530
Nothing's been moved...

00:47:29.770 --> 00:47:31.470
We treasured it,

00:47:33.030 --> 00:47:36.500
hoping that you might
come back one day,

00:47:38.700 --> 00:47:40.400
no matter which form you take.

00:47:47.400 --> 00:47:51.630
Is there really no way
for Beam to stay with us longer?

00:47:53.700 --> 00:47:54.930
I have no clue.

00:47:56.800 --> 00:47:58.270
But if there's one,

00:47:58.830 --> 00:47:59.970
I'd like to do it.

00:48:01.100 --> 00:48:03.970
Beam has an unfortunate fate.

00:48:08.300 --> 00:48:09.500
Beam, wanna come sit with me?

00:48:25.070 --> 00:48:27.070
I have something important to tell you.

00:48:31.100 --> 00:48:32.770
I have something I want to tell you.

00:48:34.970 --> 00:48:38.400
It's our family secret

00:48:39.300 --> 00:48:41.170
that has been kept for 20 years.

00:48:42.700 --> 00:48:46.330
I want to make sure you know.

00:48:48.730 --> 00:48:50.030
In reality...

00:48:52.470 --> 00:48:54.270
I'm not your older sister.

00:49:03.200 --> 00:49:04.670
You're not my sister.

00:49:06.130 --> 00:49:07.330
You're my daughter.

00:49:08.170 --> 00:49:09.830
My only daughter.

00:49:14.030 --> 00:49:15.230
Huh?!

00:49:29.800 --> 00:49:30.730
Z!

00:49:30.730 --> 00:49:31.930
Are you okay?

00:49:31.930 --> 00:49:32.870
Are you still having a headache?

00:49:34.130 --> 00:49:35.600
Tadaaaaa~

00:49:36.630 --> 00:49:39.670
This is my Shio-Pan shop.

00:49:40.100 --> 00:49:43.830
I think you should spend

00:49:43.830 --> 00:49:48.400
whatever time you left with your family.

00:49:48.700 --> 00:49:52.170
I shouldn't have told her

00:49:52.300 --> 00:49:56.670
Look! Her smile don't reach her eyes.

00:49:56.970 --> 00:50:00.100
And then you rest your head on me like this